// Error: A<->X/Y transfer with a known M/X width mismatch.
//
// `tax`/`tay`/`txa`/`tya` move the full register width. When the accumulator
// and index widths are both known but differ, only half the value is moved
// and the other half silently keeps its previous contents ‚Äî almost always a
// bug. If either width is unknown the programmer is presumed to know what
// they're doing and no error fires (see syntax-mode-transfer-width-deferred).

func bad @a8 @i16 {
    tax
}

func main @a8 @i8 {
    nop
}
